## Thread 12 — `HistoricalDataExistsFilter` not working (Mithra) — *needs your input*

> After investigating this, I found the root cause: the 334 existing documents for `AT0000A0U299_186` in `muse-derived` all have `"HISTORICAL_DATE": ""` (empty string) and `PROVIDER_DATATYPE: "DERIVED"`. The actual data date is stored in the `Calculation Date` field as `dd/MM/yyyy` (e.g. `17/05/2026`), not in `HISTORICAL_DATE`.
>
> The existence check queries `HISTORICAL_DATE = "20260430"` which always returns 0 hits on normal DERIVED docs — so the filter never fires and every security passes through.
>
> The original design relied on `enrichProcessedItem` stamping `HISTORICAL_DATE` on response docs, but you've asked us to remove that stamping (Thread 6). This creates a design conflict: the filter has no populated field to match against.
>
> **Could you confirm:** should the existence check compare the requested historical date (format `YYYYMMDD`) against the `Calculation Date` field (format `dd/MM/yyyy`)? I can implement the format conversion and fix the query accordingly. Alternatively, if there is another field that should be used as the date anchor for deduplication, please point us to it and we'll fix it immediately.

